Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. In a #small pot{}, combine 1¼ cups water and @salt{pinch}; bring to a boil. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}(minced) until you have 1 TBSP. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} to #pot{}. Cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve. Meanwhile, toss @broccoli florets{8%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until tender and crisped, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned, ~{5-7%minutes} per side (it'll cook through in the next step). Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together ¼ cup water, @cornstarch{1%tsp}, @honey{2%tbsp}, and @soy sauce{2%tbsp} until very smooth. Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-low heat. Add garlic, ginger, and scallion whites. Cook, stirring, until fragrant and slightly softened, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}.

Pour half the @white wine vinegar{5%tsp} into pan and simmer until almost evaporated. Stir in sauce and bring to a boil. Let bubble until thickened, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Stir in 1 tsp @sesame oil{1%tbsp}. Return chicken to pan and reduce heat to medium low; turn to coat in sauce. Continue cooking until sauce thickens and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If sauce is too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt. Stir in 1 tsp remaining sesame oil, then divide between plates. Top with chicken and add broccoli to the side. Spoon any remaining sauce over chicken. Garnish with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}.